(44, 5, 16, 42, 9, 11, 11, NULL, 'Healing Ministry of Jesus and Apostles', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of those in need. Acts 5:16 describes the healing of sick and possessed individuals, while Luke 9:11 highlights Jesus healing those who followed him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 16, 43, 14, 12, 12, 'healed every one', 'Healing and Belief Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing through belief. In Acts 5:16, the sick are healed, while John 14:12 emphasizes that believers will perform similar works, indicating a continuity of miraculous acts through faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 17, 44, 13, 45, 45, NULL, 'Indignation and Envy in Opposition', 'This connection highlights the emotional responses of the religious leaders in both passages. In Acts 5:17, the Sadducees are ''filled with indignation,'' while in Acts 13:45, the Jews are ''filled with envy,'' indicating a shared theme of opposition to the apostles'' teachings.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 17, 44, 7, 9, 9, 'filled with indignation', 'Indignation and Envy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of envy leading to harmful actions. In Acts 5:17, the Sadducees'' indignation parallels the patriarchs'' envy in Acts 7:9, both resulting in unjust treatment of others.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 17, 60, 2, 1, 1, 'filled with indignation', 'Indignation and Malice Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of negative emotions. The high priest and Sadducees'' ''indignation'' parallels the call to lay aside ''malice'' in 1 Peter.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 17, 9, 18, 12, 16, 'filled with indignation', 'Fear of Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize fear stemming from divine favor. In Acts, the Sadducees'' indignation reflects their fear of the apostles'' influence, similar to Saul''s fear of David due to the Lord being with him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 17, 18, 5, 2, 2, 'filled with indignation', 'Indignation and Wrath Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of destructive emotions. Both passages emphasize how negative feelings, such as indignation and wrath, can lead to harmful consequences for individuals.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 17, 19, 2, 1, 3, 'filled with indignation', 'Indignation and Raging Against Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of opposition to divine authority. Both passages emphasize the rulers'' anger and their desire to break free from the constraints imposed by God and His anointed.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 17, 20, 14, 30, 30, 'filled with indignation', 'Indignation and Envy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of emotional states leading to negative consequences. The ''indignation'' of the Sadducees in Acts reflects a similar destructive quality as ''envy'' in Proverbs, both suggesting how such feelings can corrupt one''s well-being.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
