(44, 5, 18, 66, 2, 10, 10, 'put them in the common prison', 'Prison and Suffering Connection', 'Both passages emphasize imprisonment as a trial for believers. Acts 5:18 describes apostles being imprisoned, while Revelation 2:10 warns of imprisonment as a test of faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 19, 44, 16, 26, 26, 'opened the prison doors', 'Prison Deliverance Motif', 'Both passages emphasize miraculous prison openings, showcasing divine intervention. The angel''s action in Acts 5 parallels the earthquake''s effect in Acts 16.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 19, 19, 34, 7, 7, 'the angel of the Lord', 'Divine Deliverance by Angels', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the angel of the Lord in delivering those who fear Him. Acts 5:19 describes an angel freeing imprisoned apostles, while Psalms 34:7 speaks of the angel encamping around those who revere God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 19, 19, 105, 17, 20, NULL, 'Divine Deliverance from Imprisonment', 'Both passages emphasize divine intervention in freeing individuals from bondage. In Acts, the angel of the Lord opens prison doors, while in Psalms, the king sends to loose Joseph from fetters.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
